#: Game.Levels.L24Levels.L05
msgid "# Level 5: Heine-Borel Theorem: Part 2b\n"
"\n"
"**The Grand Finale**: We'll complete Heine-Borel by proving that any closed, bounded set is compact. The strategy is elegant: show that closed subsets of compact sets are compact, then use Level 4.\n"
"\n"
"**New Lean Technology - Sum Types** ­¤ō”\n"
"\n"
"Before diving into the proof, you need to master Lean's **disjoint union** (sum type):\n"
"\n"
"**What is ┬¦0?**: It's the \"either ┬¦1 or ┬¦2\" type - every element is either from type ┬¦3 or from type ┬¦4, but not both. Think of it as two boxes labeled \"Left\" and \"Right\":\n"
"\n"
"┬¦5\n"
"\n"
"**Note**:\n"
"- ┬¦6 puts element ┬¦7 into the \"left\" side\n"
"- ┬¦8 puts element ┬¦9 into the \"right\" side\n"
"\n"
"**Pattern Matching with ┬¦10**: To make a function on a sum type, use ┬¦11:\n"
"\n"
"┬¦12\n"
"\n"
"**Case Analysis with ┬¦13**: When arguing about where an element of a sum type came from, use ┬¦14:\n"
"\n"
"┬¦15\n"
"\n"
"**Extracting Components**: If ┬¦16, then:\n"
"- ┬¦17 extracts all the \"left\" elements\n"
"- ┬¦18\n"
"\n"
"**Why Sum Types for This Proof?**\n"
"\n"
"We need to handle TWO kinds of balls simultaneously:\n"
"1. **Original balls** (type ┬¦19) that cover our closed set ┬¦20\n"
"2. **Avoidance balls** (type ┬¦21) that cover points outside ┬¦22\n"
"\n"
"The sum type ┬¦23 lets us create a unified covering system!\n"
"\n"
"**The Strategy**:\n"
"1. Start with any covering of closed set ┬¦24 where ┬¦25 is compact\n"
"2. Since ┬¦26 is closed, ┬¦27 is open - so each point in ┬¦28 has a ball staying in ┬¦29\n"
"3. Use sum types to combine: original balls + avoidance balls = covering of all ┬¦30 (in fact, all of ┬¦31)\n"
"4. Apply compactness of ┬¦32 to get finite subcover\n"
"5. Extract just the \"left\" (original) balls to cover ┬¦33, since avoidance balls don't touch ┬¦34\n"
"\n"
"**Your Mission**: Master sum types and use them to extend any covering of a closed subset to a covering of the whole compact set. This completes the Heine-Borel theorem!"
msgstr ""

