#: Game.Levels.L3Levels.L02_OneOverN
msgid "# Level 2: Our First Real Limit\n"
"\n"
"*Congratulations!* You've just proved the Archimedean Property. Now let's use it to prove something genuinely interesting: our first non-trivial limit.\n"
"\n"
"## The Goal: Proving that ┬¦0\n"
"\n"
"We want to prove that the sequence ┬¦1 converges to ┬¦2 as ┬¦3 approaches infinity. This is intuitively obviousŌĆöas ┬¦4 gets larger, ┬¦5 gets smaller and approaches ┬¦6. But how do we make this rigorous using the ┬¦7-┬¦8 definition of limits?\n"
"\n"
"**Theorem**: The sequence ┬¦9 converges to ┬¦10.\n"
"\n"
"This might seem straightforward, but let's see it as a test of the definition.\n"
"\n"
"## Recall: The Definition of Sequential Convergence\n"
"\n"
"A sequence ┬¦11 converges to a limit ┬¦12 (written ┬¦13) if:\n"
"\n"
