"- **Arithmetic with inequalities**: You might also find the ┬¦75 tactic helpful. It is a very powerful, general tactic like ┬¦76, but instead of proving algebraic *identities*, it proves *inequalities* involving \"linear arithmetic\" on the specified hypotheses. For example,\n"
