"The forward direction was straightforward: we had ┬¦5 from the function limit and used it directly.\n"
"\n"
"For the backward direction, we use **proof by contradiction**:\n"
"- Assume ┬¦6 is false\n"
"- Then ┬¦7 such that ┬¦8, ┬¦9 with ┬¦10, ┬¦11, but ┬¦12\n"
"- We'll construct a **problematic sequence** by choosing such an ┬¦13 for each ┬¦14\n"
"- This sequence converges to ┬¦15 but ┬¦16 does *not* converge to ┬¦17, contradicting our hypothesis!\n"
"\n"
"## The Proof Strategy\n"
"\n"
"**Given:** ┬¦18\n"
"\n"
"**Want:** ┬¦19, i.e., ┬¦20\n"
"\n"
"**Proof by contradiction:**\n"
"1. **Assume negation:** ┬¦21 such that ┬¦22, the implication fails\n"
"2. **Extract witnesses:** Use ┬¦23 to get ┬¦24 and a function ┬¦25 that produces counterexamples\n"
"3. **Construct sequence:** Define ┬¦26 with ┬¦27 and ┬¦28\n"
"4. **Show convergence:** Prove ┬¦29 (since ┬¦30)\n"
"5. **Apply hypothesis:** Get ┬¦31 from our assumption\n"
"6. **Derive contradiction:** This contradicts ┬¦32\n"
"\n"
"## Your Challenge\n"
