"\n"
"## The Big Question\n"
"\n"
"You've proven: **convergence Ō¤╣ Cauchy**\n"
"\n"
"But what about the converse? Is every Cauchy sequence convergent?\n"
"\n"
"- **For rational sequences**: NO! The sequence ┬¦4 is Cauchy in ŌäÜ but doesn't converge to a rational number.\n"
"- **For real sequences**: This is the *Cauchy Completeness Theorem*, and it's **YES**! But we'll need to carefully construct the real numbers first to prove it.\n"
"\n"
"This is why Cauchy sequences are so importantŌĆöthey give us a way to *define* the real numbers as the completion of the rationals!\n"
"\n"
"Onward to the next level!"
msgstr ""

