#: Game.Levels.L12Levels.L00_SubseqIterate
msgid "# Level 1: Iterated Subsequence\n"
"\n"
"Let's warm up to the topics of this lecture with a foundational exercise.\n"
"\n"
"Suppose you have a sequence of natural numbers, ┬¦0, and all you know about it is that it always exceeds the identity:\n"
"\n"
"┬¦1\n"
"\n"
"This doesn't mean that ┬¦2 is itself strictly increasing (what we call a ┬¦3). The sequence could jump around all over the place, as long as its graph stays above that of ┬¦4.\n"
"\n"
