"**The Setup**: We have a uniformly continuous function on ┬¦0 - that is, there's a single ┬¦1 such that whenever two points are within ┬¦2 of each other, the function values differ by at most ┬¦3.\n"
"\n"
"**The Question**: If we refine our Riemann sum partition from ┬¦4 subintervals to ┬¦5 subintervals, how much can the Riemann sum change?\n"
