"**The Intuition**: When we go from ┬¦6 to ┬¦7 subintervals, we're making the partition finer. If our original partition was already fine enough (meaning ┬¦8), then the sample points in the refined partition shouldn't be too far from the corresponding sample points in the coarse partition. By uniform continuity, this means the function values shouldn't differ by much either.\n"
